meanings.definition: To dress in a more stylish or elegant manner than someone else.
meanings.sent1: She outdressed her friend at the party with her beautiful gown.
meanings.sent2: The fashion model always outdressed everyone on the runway.
meanings.sent3: At the costume party, she outdressed even the most extravagant costumes.
meanings.sent4: Her sense of style outdressed the entire fashion industry.
meanings.sent5: Her outfit outdressed all the others, making her the center of attention.

meanings.definition: To surpass in dressing or appearance.
meanings.sent1: He outdressed his colleagues at the office with his sharp suit.
meanings.sent2: The celebrity always outdressed the paparazzi with her stunning outfits.
meanings.sent3: The peacock outdressed all the other birds in the forest with its vibrant feathers.
meanings.sent4: Her confidence outdressed any outfit she wore.
meanings.sent5: The elegant ball gown outdressed all the other dresses at the event.
